<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391503>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A–F, Lathahypossia aculeata (Busulini, Tessier & Visentin, 1984), from the Middle Eocene of the Cava Main, Arzignano (northeast Italy). A–E, male, MSNVE-27378: A, dorsal view; B, ventral view; C, frontal view, D, posterior view; E, right lateral view. F, male, MSNVE-27377, ventral view. Abbreviations, s: pleonal somites; st: thoracic sternites; t: telson. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391503/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391507>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A–G, Lathahypossia aculeata (Busulini, Tessier & Visentin, 1984), from the Middle Eocene of the Cava Main, Arzignano (NE Italy). A, B, D–F, male, MSNVE-27378: A, view of sub-cephalic region; B, view of endostomial region; D, detail of pleon; E–G, detail and close-up of ‘press-button’, male pleonal locking mechanism. C, male, MSNVE-27377, detail of anterior part of sternum. Abbreviations, aa: basal antennular article; ab: basal antennal article; en: endostome; ep; epistome; er: endostomial ridge; ex: exopod of third maxilliped; is: ischium of third maxilliped; mxp3: third maxilliped; P1: first pereopod; pb: ‘press-button’; s: pleonal somites; st: thoracic sternites. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391507/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A, B, Lathahypossia aculeata (Busulini, Tessier & Visentin, 1984), holotype, MSNVE-25083, from the Middle Eocene of the Cava Main, Arzignano (northeast Italy). A, dorsal view; B, frontal view. Scale bar = 10 mm (pictures by G. Tessier)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

